pr_body:
Closes #39.

@jaimegildesagredo please take a look and tell me if this is what you wanted. I've preserved the tests comparing integers and added a couple of tests that make sure the method used for comparison is `__ne__` when testing for negated equality.

Otherwise I will keep trying :)

The only significant change from the existing deployer
is that the old deployer treated a scheduled event as
a single resource whereas the new deployer treats it as
two separate resources: a lambda function and a cloudwatch
event.  The main benefit of this approach is that you can
reuse existing logic for building/planning a lambda
function.

Just to give you an idea of what the `deployed.json` looks like,
given this app:

```python
from chalice import Chalice

app = Chalice(app_name='james7')


@app.schedule('rate(100 hours)')
def index(event):
    return {'hello': 'world'}
```

You get this `deployed.json` file:

```json
{
  "stages": {
    "dev": {
      "resources": [
        {
          "role_arn": "arn:aws:iam::312063461226:role/james7-dev",
          "name": "default-role",
          "resource_type": "iam_role"
        },
        {
          "lambda_arn": "arn:aws:lambda:us-west-2:123:function:james7-dev-index",
          "name": "index",
          "resource_type": "lambda_function"
        },
        {
          "rule_name": "james7-dev-index-event",
          "name": "index-event",
          "resource_type": "cloudwatch_event"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "schema_version": "2.0"
}
```

@jonparrott Asked that I make a "do not merge" PR out of this, as a placeholder for the work remaining in #1998.

When I wrote this code (May 10th), the system tests all passed without issue, but the unit tests are currently very broken by this change.

I am very much intentionally leaving the "Allow edits from maintainers" box checked, so anyone is free to fix the unit tests :grinning:
